column10: Electrify your sneaker rotation with the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Static. This Yeezy 350 V2 comes with a grey and white upper and a white sole. These sneakers released in December 2018 and retailed for $220. You can see what socks you’re wearing in this shoe…so please Buy them now on StockX.

Compliment the Coachella fit with the adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Oil. This Yeezy Boot comes with an oil upper, oil midsole, and an oil sole. These sneakers released in April 2019 and retailed for $200. Buy some fresh boots for Sunday Service, right here on StockX.

column2: Nike Air Zoom GT Cut 3 Smoke
column10:
Lightweight and durable, the Nike Air Zoom GT Cut 3 Smoke sneakers deliver a responsive performance for basketballers that need quick turns and a spring in their step.

With Zoom X cushioning along the length of the shoe, the Nike Air zoom GT’s are a great fit for ballers who need extra bounce on the court. The outsole is sticky with rubber in a herringbone design to provide the ultimate traction, and the silhouette provides a stable support when needed most. A good-looking shoe in a dark Smoke color, with black, white and gray accents, the laces are black and the Nike text sits on the back heel. A giant white Swoosh brands the inner and outers, and the shoe has a tongue pull tag with the wording GT Cut 3.

We love the slick, moody look the color combo delivers with the Air Zoom Smoke trainers. A hardy shoe for professionals as much as urban trend-setters, the Nike Air Zoom GT Cut 3 Smoke was released on January 10, 2024, retailed at $190.

column2: Jordan 1 Low SE White Legend Blue
column10:
The Jordan 1 Low SE White Legend Blue offers a new colorway in this iconic line of sneakers. All the premium materials remain embellished with subtle detail. Its crisp design complements the classic silhouette of one of the world's most beloved shoes.

All the dependable Air Jordan technology is here, including the Nike Air cushioning. The upper combines real and synthetic leather with toe perforations that provide breathability. The base color is white, with shiny, light blue panels and Swoosh. The latter matches the high-grip rubber undersole.

Our reviewers always welcome a new version of this classic trainer. The embroidered Wings logo on the heel gives it a special touch. This shoe has the familiar, solid yet lightweight feel we've come to expect from the AJ1 line. It's one to add to any collection and a perfect introduction to the range. The Jordan 1 Low SE White Legend Blue was released on October 1, 2024, for $125.

column2: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Spider-Man Across the Spider-Verse
column10:
Nike and Jordan Brand are returning back to the Spider-Verse for their second Spider-Man themed Air Jordan 1, with the release of the Air Jordan 1 High OG Spider-Man Across the Spider-Verse.

Also known as the Next Chapter, the Jordan 1 High OG Spider-Man Across the Spider-Verse is the next iteration of the original Air Jordan 1 Chicago colorway. The limited edition sneakers are constructed using various leathers, suedes, and other premium materials across the uppers. The patterns used across the sneakers are designed to mimic the Miles Morales/Spider-Man animation style.

The Air Jordan 1 High OG Spider-Man Across the Spider-Verse released May 20, 2023, with a retail price of $200.

Nike SB’s collaboration with Jordan helps create the ultimate sneaker for the skatepark to the basketball court, with the release of the Jordan 4 Retro SB Pine Green.

The Jordan 4 Retro SB Pine Green used a white leather upper with a Neutral Grey suede mudguard. The limited edition sneakers sit on top of a white and Pine Green midsole which is highlighted by a red air unit. Nike used a gum outsole to help with increased grip while skateboarding.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro SB Pine Green released March 20, 2023, with a retail price of $225.

The classic Air Jordan 3 silhouette comes to life in this sleek iteration — the Jordan 3 Retro OG Rare Air (GS). The robust black base creates a moody statement shoe that reminds fans of the rarity of this OG shape and style.

With a primarily black leather base, an Elephant Gray front panel, and accents in Chili Red, Military Blue, light gray, and Coconut Milk, this high-top is a throwback to the original design from 1988. With a perforated tongue branding a red Jumpman logo, the Rare Air (GS) Jordan 3 Retro OG is otherwise clear of branding, apart from the mirrored Nike Air on the heel, which is also red. The midsoles show clear shock panels, and the upper collars have touches of blue mesh. Additional gray lace holes sit on the sides of the lace structure.

We love how strong these Nike Air OG’s present. With a bold color combination, the leather shoes are perfect for both dressier occasions and everyday lifestyle wear. The Air Jordan 3 Retro OG Rare Air (GS) sneakers were released on May 30, 2025, for $150.

column2: Jordan 1 Low Black Toe Medium Olive
column10:
Slicker than your average, the Jordan 1 Low Black Toe Medium Olive is an instant classic kick. The perfect lifestyle sneaker to fit the wardrobes of modern streetwear fans, clean lines and simplicity of design make this shoe a must-have for collectors.

The bar has been risen with the Air Jordan 1 Lows. In sophisticated olive, black and white on the colorways, the Black Toe Mediu m Olive Jordan 1 Low is as elegant as it is functional. As a low-top, the shoe provides a mature silhouette, whilst still throwing a nod to the athletic stylings of the original Air Jordan shape. The Jumpman logo features on the tongue and the Wings logo is branded on the back heel, making these leather sneakers minimalist and a fantastic heritage addition to your footwear collection.

We love the strong, yet understated design of these low Air Jordans. A great pair for your lifestyle sneaker collection, the colors make them suitable for dressier occasions, work, or dates. The Jordan 1 Low Black Toe Medium Olive was released on 20 September 2024, priced at $115.

The Nike Kobe 8 Protro Lakers Away is a bold new release that combines legendary performance with iconic Lakers flair. Featuring a sleek black engineered knit upper, this colorway brings the energy of a Lakers away game to the court. Gold embroidered Nike swooshes and Kobe Bryant’s signature in gold on the black heel clip add a touch of luxury, while the white outsole provides contrast against the black midsole. This Lakers-inspired colorway brings the competitive intensity of Kobe's road performances to life.

As part of the Kobe Protro line, the Kobe 8 continues to offer cutting-edge technology while paying homage to one of the most beloved basketball sneakers ever made. The Protro updates include advanced cushioning and materials, making this sneaker a top choice for athletes and sneakerheads alike. The performance-driven design, combined with the sleek look of the Lakers Away colorway, makes this a standout addition to any Kobe collection.

Released on September 6, 2024, the Nike Kobe 8 Protro Lakers Away retailed at $190. The black, university gold, white, and court purple colorway pays tribute to the Lakers’ iconic uniforms. Whether on the court or in your rotation, this Kobe 8 Protro is a must-have for fans of the Black Mamba and basketball culture.

column2: adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA Triple Black
column10:
The adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA Triple Black is a new colorway of the Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA line of sneakers.

The Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA Triple Black features a Primeknit upper that is both flexible and breathable, allowing for a snug fit that will keep your feet comfortable and supported no matter how long your run or workout. The shoe also features a Boost midsole, which offers energy return and cushioning, making it perfect for those who need protection from the impact of running, jumping, and other high-intensity activities. The shoe's Continental rubber outsole provides traction on both wet and dry surfaces, giving you the confidence to tackle any terrain with ease.

We think that the standout feature of the adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 DNA Triple Black is its sleek design. The use of black on black gives the shoe a clean and minimalist look that is both stylish and understated. The shoe was released on November 30th, 2022 at a retail price of $200.

Michael Jordan is paying homage to his alma mater, The University of North Carolina, with the release of the Air Jordan 5 Retro UNC University Blue.

The Jordan 5 UNC comes in the Tar Heels signature University Blue across the uppers and is dressed with University Blue laces, and lace locks. A black midsole with white and University Blue detailing separates the translucent blue outsole from the suede uppers. The sneakers are topped off with a silver reflective 3M tongue with a black jumpman logo.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro UNC University Blue released March 5, 2023, with a retail price of $225.

Please Note: Both plastic shoe trees are required for verification.
Jordan Brand brings back a monument of Jordan hype with the Air Jordan 11 Retro Playoffs Bred, now available on StockX. These sneakers represent MJ’s comeback from retirement to win his fourth title with the Chicago Bulls and the 1996 Finals MVP. This is the fourth time this colorway has been retroed since it’s original debut.

This Jordan 11 features a black upper with shiny patent leather overlays and red detailing. A red translucent outsole, white midsole, and "23" insignia on the heel completes the design. These sneakers released in November of 2019 and retailed for $220.

column2: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Lucky Green
column10:
Jordan Brand continued its pattern of Lucky Green colorways in early 2023, with the release of the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Lucky Green. The Air Jordan 1 is the third model to receive the Lucky Green treatment following the Jordan 2 and Jordan 3.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG is constructed using a leather upper, brought to life with shades of white, black and Lucky Green throughout. Lucky Green Nike branding sits on top of the black tongue and insoles of the sneaker. The sneakers are tied together with Lucky Green laces.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Lucky Green released April 15, 2023, with a retail price of $180.

Making a splash on May 31, 2023, the adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Teal are the epitome of innovation and style. These unique sneakers are drenched in the Stone Teal colorway, a hypnotic blend of earthy hues that make the shoe a standout in any setting.

With a design that challenges conventional sneaker architecture, the 450's offer an avant-garde aesthetic highlighted by an intricately woven upper nestled in an eccentric, claw-like sole. The shoes embrace comfort, with the sock-like construction ensuring an effortlessly snug fit. The adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Teal isn't just a shoe; it's a statement piece, guaranteed to turn heads and garner compliments. Let these sneakers elevate your style game, providing a distinctive edge that's unmatched in the sneaker world.

The adidas Yeezy 450 Stone Teal hit the streets on May 31, 2023, carrying a retail price of $210.

The Jordan 12 Retro Melo (GS) is a stylish and comfortable sneaker designed for young athletes and fashion-forward kids. Featuring a crisp white leather upper with university blue accents, these shoes pay homage to NBA star Carmelo Anthony's signature colorway. The iconic Jordan 12 silhouette is enhanced with metallic silver detailing, creating a sleek and eye-catching look that's sure to turn heads on and off the court.

These sneakers aren't just about looks - they're built for performance too. The full-length Zoom Air unit provides responsive cushioning, while the durable rubber outsole offers excellent traction for quick cuts and sudden stops. The padded collar and tongue ensure a snug, comfortable fit, making these shoes perfect for all-day wear. Our team thinks this product is great for young basketball enthusiasts looking to emulate their favorite players while enjoying superior comfort and style.

The Jordan 1 Low 85 Neutral Grey represents an effort by Nike to return to the brand’s vintage roots. The sneaker finds inspiration in Michael Jordan’s first lifestyle sneaker, the Air Jordan 1 released in 1985, but bears a similar resemblance to the Nike Dunk Low.

Several details highlight the shoe’s vintage aesthetic, including the lightly pre-yellowed midsole that provides a worn-in appearance. The sneaker features a leather upper, perforations across the vamp, and a prominent Swoosh on the side. The Summit White, Light Smoke Grey, Neutral Grey, and Sail color blocking is similar to the OG version, but the grey tones are darker.

Our experts love that the Jordan 1 85 Neutral Grey updates the Air Jordan 1 Low OG Neutral Grey released in 2020. Unlike the first reissue of the OG model, the Jordan 1 85 Neutral Grey version offers more details that pay homage to the sneakers of 1985. The Jordan 1 Low 85 Neutral Grey was released on October 25, 2023, and retailed at $170.

Introducing the Jordan 1 Retro High OG Latte (Women's), a sneaker that blends classic style with a modern twist, perfect for today's fashion-forward crowd. This edition features a tasteful mix of Black, Legend Medium Brown, White, and Sail, reflecting a sophisticated palette that’s as versatile as it is striking. The high-top silhouette maintains its legendary profile, updated with a fresh color scheme that resonates with the subtle yet bold tastes of a new generation.

This Jordan 1 Retro High OG is designed not just for looks but also for lasting comfort. The high-quality leather upper and air-cushioned sole provide premium support and durability, making it ideal for daily wear. Whether you're stepping out for a night on the town or heading to a casual meetup, these sneakers are crafted to offer both standout style and practical functionality.

Released on May 29, 2024, the Jordan 1 Retro High OG Latte (Women's) retailed for $180. This sneaker has quickly become a staple in the collections of those who appreciate a refined approach to streetwear. With its neutral yet impactful colorway and classic design, it promises to remain a favorite for years to come, showcasing a timeless charm that transcends seasons and trends.

column2: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Black Phantom
column10:
Travis Scott closed out 2022 with the return of his signature Jordan 1 Low, this time in a new Black Phantom colorway.

The silhouette returned with his signature backwards Nike Swoosh but with a new contrast stitch design. The all black nubuck sneakers feature a Nike Air logo on the tongue and an Air Jordan Wings logo on the right heel tab. Red, Black, and White/Black laces are included and an embroidered Bee is located on the heel tab of the left sneaker inspired by Travis’ daughter, Stormi.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Black Phantom released December 15, 2022 with a retail price of $150.
